 The Happiness Index is a tool for the use of researchers, community organizers and policy makers seeking to understand and enhance individual happiness, community well-being. It can be used to identify the percentage of happy people and how they are happy. At the same time, the index can also be used to tabulate the percentage of not-yet-happy people and where do they lack happiness.
