        <h4>Freedom to make choices</h4>
        <p>1) Another key feature of a society is the freedom that it provides to its members. No people can be
            truly happy if they do not feel that they are choosing the course of their own life always of course to
            the inevitable constraints of human existence.
            2) Private freedom is measured absence of restrictions on choice in the personal sphere of life, such
            as travel etc.
            3) Psychological freedom is a lack of inner restrictions for seizing opportunities to choose. A first
            inner constraint is low self-esteem.
            
            </p>
      </div>
    </div>            
</div>
